7 An Act relating to poor persons; modifying provisions
related to the 2-1-1 Collaborative; modifying
8 membership of Collaborative; providing appointing
authority; allowing for reappointment; and providing
9 an effective date.
10
11 AUTHOR: Add the following House Coauthor: Waldron
12 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Page 1, strike the title, enacting clause and
entire bill and insert
13
14 “An Act relating to 2-1-1 services; amending 56 O.S.
2021, Section 3021, which relates to the Oklahoma 2-
15 1-1 Collaborative; removing obsolete language;
specifying certain services of 2-1-1 call centers;
16 placing the Collaborative under the administrative
oversight of the Department of Human Services;
17 modifying and removing certain powers and duties;
modifying membership of the Collaborative; specifying
18 procedures for appointment, reappointment, removal,
and vacancy of members; creating certain exclusion
19 for specified contracts; and providing an effective
date.
20
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
23 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 56 O.S. 2021, Section 3021, is
24 amended to read as follows:
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4095 Page 1

1 Section 3021. A. Beginning on January 1, 2011, the Oklahoma 2-
2 1-1 Advisory Collaborative shall be renamed the 2-1-1 Oklahoma
3 Coordinating Council. Beginning on July 1, 2021, the 2-1-1 Oklahoma
4 Coordinating Council shall be renamed the Oklahoma 2-1-1
5 Collaborative. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative is hereby
6 designated as the state lead entity of all 2-1-1 call centers in
7 this state that provide hotline services including, but not limited
8 to, support for food, housing, clothing, transportation, and medical
9 needs.
10 B. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative, under the administrative
11 oversight of the Department of Human Services, shall have the
12 following duties and responsibilities:
13 1. Develop and maintain Provide recommendations for a statewide
14 coordinated approach for the promotion of a 2-1-1 system;
15 2. Develop and maintain Provide recommendations for an
16 integrated statewide 2-1-1 service that avoids overlap of 2-1-1 call
17 centers in the state;
18 3. Certify Verify that information and referral providers who
19 wish to become 2-1-1 call centers meet applicable national
20 accreditation standards;
21 4. Develop and maintain certification standards for providers
22 that operate as a 2-1-1 call center in the state in compliance with
23 the Alliance for Information and Referral Systems;
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4095 Page 2

1 5. Assure that each 2-1-1 call center is accountable and
2 maintains compliance with Corporation Commission standards;
3 6. Develop and maintain a process for 2-1-1 call center
4 accountability and compliance with state and national standards for
5 any contractual obligations;
6 7. 5. Provide leadership and coordination for 2-1-1 call
7 centers as it relates to large-scale emergencies and homeland
8 security needs;
9 8. Develop and implement
10 6. Provide recommendations for a statewide, outcome-driven
11 strategic plan for 2-1-1 Oklahoma;
12 9. 7. Advocate for funding to support and sustain 2-1-1 system
13 delivery;
14 10. 8. Coordinate with national, state and local partners in
15 the provision of 2-1-1 services;
16 11. 9. Collaborate with such entities as may be required and to
17 the extent required under federal law or to receive federal funding;
18 12. 10. Provide funding formula recommendations to the
19 administering entity responsible Department of Human Services for
20 the allocation of direct state and federal funds appropriated for 2-
21 1-1 Oklahoma; and
22 13. 11. Submit an annual report no later than September 1 of
23 each year to the cabinet Secretary for the cabinet area consisting
24 of the Department of Human Services, of the services rendered in the
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4095 Page 3

1 past fiscal year by the 2-1-1 system. The report may also include
2 recommendations of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative.
3 C. 1. The membership of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall
4 be comprised of fifteen (15) nine (9) members, five of whom shall be
5 public sector representatives and ten of whom shall be private
6 sector representatives. The initial members shall be selected by
7 the current 2-1-1 call centers in this state as of the effective
8 date of this act. Vacancies that occur after the selection of the
9 initial members shall be filled by the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative
10 as follows:
11 a. the Director of Human Services or designee,
12 b. the Director of the Oklahoma Department of Emergency
13 Management or designee,
14 c. the State Commissioner of Health or designee, and
15 d. six private sector representatives. The Governor, the
16 President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker
17 of the House of Representatives shall each appoint one
18 such member who resides in the 2-1-1 service area for
19 western Oklahoma and one such member who resides in
20 the 2-1-1 service area for eastern Oklahoma.
21 2. The initial appointments of the private sector
22 representatives described in subparagraph d of paragraph 1 of this
23 subsection shall be made as follows:
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4095 Page 4

1 a. the Governor shall appoint two members to serve
2 initial terms of one (1) year each,
3 b. the President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall appoint
4 one member to serve an initial term of two (2) years
5 and one member to serve an initial term of three (3)
6 years, and
7 c. the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall
8 appoint one member to serve an initial term of two (2)
9 years and one member to serve an initial term of three
10 (3) years.
11 Thereafter, such members shall serve terms of three (3) years and
12 may be reappointed. Such members may be removed by their appointing
13 authorities for cause. Any vacancy shall be filled by the
14 appointing authority for the remainder of the unexpired term.
15 3. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall meet not less than
16 two times per year for the purpose of reviewing and carrying out its
17 duties and responsibilities.
18 3. 4. The members of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall
19 adopt by-laws governing its operations including terms of office,
20 the conduct of meetings and such other functions as the Oklahoma 2-
21 1-1 Collaborative deems necessary to carry out its duties and
22 responsibilities.
23
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4095 Page 5

1 4. 5. Members shall serve without compensation or reimbursement
2 for expenses; provided, that members who are public officers may be
3 reimbursed for necessary expenses as provided by law.
4 D. If federal funding related to 2-1-1 services becomes
5 available to the state, the state may comply with any requirements
6 necessary to make application for and receive such federal funding.
7 E. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall not have jurisdiction
8 over any statewide contract or competitively bid contract, and
9 nothing in this section shall otherwise be construed to apply to any
10 such contract.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.”
12 Passed the Senate the 4th day of May, 2026.
